[recto] Bruegel: Parable of the Blind. An adaptation of the composition with completely different background in a roundel by Lucas van Valckenborch, diam. 25,5 cm in coll. L.A. Stroink, Enschede, exhib. Almelo, Oude kunst uit Twents particulier bezit, 1953, NÂ° 52 (pl. 8); For interpretation of Parable of the Blind cf. Holbein's woodcut Christ True Light ([Arthur Bensley] Chamberlain, Hans Holbein the Younger, London: Alwin & Unwin, 1913, I, pl. 65 (opp. p. 198). The clergy of various types from Pope, Cardinal, Bishop, Monks, Parishpriest) [...]; [verso] The woodcut used in 1527 to illustrate a large broadsheet the 'Evangelistical Calendar' of Dr. Johannes Copp (Look up in B.M.).
